

graphical_graph {
    There should be a tab that renders requirement ideas and references as a force-directed web.
    The graph tab lives in the Ideas Summary webview per [webview].
    UI is implemented in ["../../../packages/extension/webviews/ideas-summary/components/GraphView.svelte"].
    Graph slices are built in ["../../../packages/analytical/src/index-store/webview-graph-queries.ts"] and served by ["../../../packages/extension/src/webview_module/ideas-summary-panel.ts"].
    By default the view focuses on the active editor file's first idea; without a focus it shows a capped slice of matching ideas rather than dumping the full graph.
    Users can filter by search text, path, @status, and tags.
    An "Indirect references" toggle expands neighbourhood depth from 1 to 2 hops.
    Clicking a node opens its source; double-click or "Focus graph" recenters the slice on that idea.
    External file references render as dashed edges to file nodes.
    A toggleable key explains node colours and edge styles.
    Pan, zoom, and drag repositioning are supported in the canvas.
    Zoom is not capped at a narrow range; users can zoom far in and far out on the canvas.
    A toggle keeps layout animation and live force-directed physics running instead of settling immediately.
}

root ["../../../packages/extension/webviews/ideas-summary/components/GraphView.svelte"]

technology {
    uses cytoscape.js for the graph layout.
}

ui_controls {
    Controls live in ["../../../packages/extension/webviews/ideas-summary/components/GraphControls.svelte"] and dispatch events to GraphView.
    The Key button toggles a draggable legend panel in ["../../../packages/extension/webviews/ideas-summary/components/GraphKeyPanel.svelte"] over the graph canvas.
}

state_machines {
    the cytoscape object should use state machines and event driven patterns
    the objects should be documented in this file.

    GraphCyMachine: ["../../../packages/extension/webviews/ideas-summary/lib/graph-cy-state.ts"] is a zustand lifecycle store.
    States: uninitialized → idle → syncing → layouting ↔ physics.
    Events: init, sync, synced, layout, layouted, physicsOn, physicsOff, destroy.
    syncGeneration cancels stale layout callbacks when the slice changes mid-layout.

    GraphNodeMachine: ["../../../packages/extension/webviews/ideas-summary/lib/graph-node-state.ts"] tracks each cytoscape node.
    States: absent → mounting → layouting → placed ↔ selected ↔ dragging.
    Events: mount, layout, place, select, deselect, dragStart, dragEnd, remove.
    GraphNodeRegistry reconciles machines on each slice sync and dispatches mount/layout/place transitions.

    GraphCyController: ["../../../packages/extension/webviews/ideas-summary/lib/graph-cy-controller.ts"] owns the cytoscape instance and dispatches GraphCyMachine events.
    syncSlice replaces elements then runs layout; requestLayout restarts the active algorithm.
    Live physics pulses cose layout on a throttled interval (not immediately on layoutstop) to avoid webview freeze.
    ResizeObserver debounces cy.resize() and does not refit on every resize.
    syncSlice and layout.run() are deferred (requestAnimationFrame / setTimeout) so the webview can paint loading state first.
}

state_machine_package {
    state machines should use xstate
}

webview_threading {
    VS Code webviews run JavaScript on a single main thread, like a browser tab.
    Heavy synchronous work — cytoscape layout iterations, large element builds, unbounded loops — blocks UI updates until it finishes.
    Layout iteration count scales with node count (capped) rather than running unbounded defaults.
    Do not restart layout synchronously on layoutstop; use throttled physics pulses instead.
}


layout_physics {
    defaults to force-directed layout (fcose) with animation on, but user inputs for other options offered by cytoscape.js
    a toggle leaves layout animation and live physics on for force-directed layouts instead of settling immediately
    
}

view_controls {
    zoom range is wide rather than tightly capped so users can inspect fine detail or see the whole neighbourhood
}

layout_options {
    - user can select from a dropdown of layout options offered by cytoscape.js
    - user can select whether to use compound layouts (where compound basis is based on the folder structure)
        - compound basis should be flexible and exptecteds as an input
}

compound_graph {
    folder hierarchy is to be supported with compound layouts
}


node_truncation {
    nodes are trunctated if there's to many
    the count should be configurable; as should the truncation basis (last changed.., last accessed.., owned by etc.)
}

physics_options {
    - user can select from a dropdown of physics options offered by cytoscape.js
        - the options for the phycis should be exposed to the user in a menu too.
    - user can select whether to use live physics/animation   
}

referenced_files_grouping {
    [referenced_files] should be grouped into a common node if they're referenced by multiple ideas.
    Line numbers should be treated like ideas if specified, such that the reference points to items in rendered graph.
    }